description: Etanna was a civitas of the Allobroges in Gallia Narbonensis and is also attested as a Roman road station. It was likely located in the modern French commune of Yenne, but its precise location is uncertain.
details: Past scholarly suggestions for siting Etanna include at the modern villages of Yenne and Etain. More recently, a rescue excavation of part of a Roman-era bathing establishment at Grand Lagneux, has suggested a third possibility.
